name: 'OH DEER' TEE
description:
Limited run of JF shirts to wear when you're out on the pints, goes well with red bull ;p

Mens shirts are orange, Ladies are pink, all shirts are printed on Gildan Heavy cotton.

All orders will be posted as soon as possible but no later than the weekend after purchase. As the run is limited it's first come first serve re: sizes, if the size you order is out of stock we can try and offer you another or fully refund the money.

name: STRUCTURES CD
description:
STRUCTURES [2011]

Track Listing:
No Reason, Just Fire
Fauxtality
If You Believe This
Reprisal
BEAST!
Structures

Produced / Mixed / Mastered by Neal Calderwood 
Artwork by Ralph Lambaco

ships with Jackalfeud Stickers and custom plectrum

*STRUCTURES PRESS QUOTES*

"One of the most exciting rock bands in the UK right now. Live they're ferocious, on record they're awesome"

Introducing - BBC Radio One

*

"Absolute Excellence, brutal in the best possible way. These are finely crafted songs, intricate and demanding attention"

Across The Line - BBC Radio Ulster 

"Jackalfeud have made giant steps in recent times. It's this new-found confidence that shines through in Structures. The EP bristles with energy and dives into big melodies with abandon. There's more than enough to keep hardcore fans happy and others more than intrigued to see what happens next" 
Alternative Ulster Magazine 

"It's a beautifully packaged, immaculately produced metal behemoth. It rages with the best of them and sees the boys make a huge leap sonically. Expect big things from this lot..."

Hot Press Magazine 

"This is a highly polished peice of work with impressive song writing and arrangement - showcasing Rowan Morrey's flawless vocals and delivery. Structures sets a high standard for accessible metal"

Big List Magazine 

"Jackalfeud are currently masters of their game"

Molten Magazine 

"[Jackalfeud] combine the best parts of what they know and what they have done before to create this little powerhouse of visceral riffs and widescreen vocals. 'Structures', much like the band, is built to last"

All Gone Pop E-zine
